            <div class="def-row"><span class="def-key">Data sources</span><span>matteoiacoviello.com/gpr (free download, monthly and daily variants).</span></div>
            <div class="def-row"><span class="def-key">Frequency</span><span>Monthly (a daily variant exists for active situations).</span></div>
            <div class="def-row"><span class="def-key">Iran 2026</span><span>~380 at the March 2026 peak, the highest of the five-year window and above the February 2022 invasion reading; still &gt;200 in July, consistent with the fragile-de-escalation scenario weighting.</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- EXTENDED INDICATOR 9: EU GAS STORAGE DEVIATION -->
        <div class="card">
          <h3>EU Gas Storage Deviation <span class="badge low">Real data</span></h3>
          <div class="chart-box" style="height:200px;"><canvas id="hist-sto"></canvas></div>
          <span class="src">EU storage fill level minus the 5-year seasonal average for the same calendar week, in percentage points (GIE AGSI+ transparency platform, free and public). The 2021 pre-crisis deficit, the 2022&ndash;24 surplus rebuilt under EU storage mandates, and the deepening deficit from the harsh 2025&ndash;26 winter into the 2026 crisis (~30% fill, roughly 30 points below norm) are all visible.</span>
          <div class="skill-panel">
            <div class="skill-head"><span class="sk-label">Predictive skill · computed backtest, overall hit rate</span><span class="sk-val" id="skval-sto">&ndash;</span></div>
            <div class="skill-box"><canvas id="skill-sto"></canvas></div>
            <span class="src">Target: next-month TTF direction. Rule: signals only when the deviation is ≤ &minus;5 points (a live deficit); a worsening deficit predicts TTF up, an improving one predicts down. Storage is the physical buffer for gas, so this is the gas-market analogue of the Redundancy Ratio.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="def-block">
            <div class="def-row"><span class="def-key">Definition</span><span><code>STO(t) = Fill%(t) &minus; SeasonalNorm(t)</code>, where the norm is the 5-year average fill level for the same calendar week. Measuring the deviation rather than the raw level removes the strong injection/withdrawal seasonality.</span></div>
            <div class="def-row"><span class="def-key">Interpretation</span><span>Within ±5 points is normal; &minus;5 to &minus;15 a live deficit that amplifies any supply shock; below &minus;15 a structural shortfall in which prices become highly event-sensitive (the 2026 configuration).</span></div>
            <div class="def-row"><span class="def-key">Data sources</span><span>GIE AGSI+ (agsi.gie.eu), free API and downloads; EU-level and per-country.</span></div>
