      <h2 class="section-title">Probabilistic Scenario Engine (Universal)</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        The engine operationalizes Method 5 for any energy situation. Prices are expressed as a <b>Price Deviation Index</b> (pre-event baseline = 100) so the same three scenario templates apply to oil, gas, LNG or power. The default calibration below uses the Iran 2026 validation case (100 ≈ $71/bbl Brent); for a new situation, only the paths and probabilities are re-estimated, the structure stays identical. The forecast horizon is fixed at eight weeks, the window over which physical rerouting, inventory response and policy reaction are observable but structural demand adjustment is not yet dominant.
      </p>

